\section{Experiments}
\subsection{Experimental Setups}
\paragraph{Timely-Eval Details}
We first introduce the components of Timely-Eval. For interactive games, We collect and wrap 57 text-based interactive games from the Jericho environment. Models are provided with tools to execute actions, query valid moves, check scores, and terminate games.
% Models must explore effectively within the time budget to maximize rewards.
General benchmarks comprise three reasoning benchmarks: AIME, MATH, and GPQA-diamond ~\cite{math, gpqa}. Models are provided with a tool to track elapsed inference time, and must adjust their reasoning strategies based on time costs and budget consumption.
ML benchmarks contain four ML tasks: Leaf Classification, Spaceship Titanic, Random Acts of Pizza, and Detecting Insults in Social Commentary. Models are allowed to use tools to execute code, obtain results, and monitor elapsed time.
